Practice, practice

</emphasis>


</title>




<para id="p1050">
I recommend that you look back into the earlier modules and convert some of 
the interactive programs listed there into scripts, execute them, and confirm 
that the scripts behave as expected. 

</para>




</section>
<section id="h21009">
<title>
<emphasis id="Cut_and_paste_programming" effect="bold">

Cut-and-paste programming

</emphasis>


</title>




<para id="p1051">
In future modules, I will switch back and forth between scripts and 
interactive mode, depending on which seems to be the most appropriate at the 
time. 

</para>




<para id="p1052">
I am a strong advocate of cut-and-paste programming. Cut-and-paste programming works well with scripts, and not so well with 
interactive mode. 

</para>




<para id="p1053">
Therefore, any time there is very much typing involved, you can usually 
expect to see me using scripts instead of interactive mode. 

</para>



	

